commitResults.messageTitle: Add echo feature, refactor greet and exit
Add store and list messages feature and refactor
commitResults.messageBody:
Chatbot commands are now exclusively lower case.

This is to keep behaviour consistent in supporting future commands.

Looping behaviour is no longer separated to a function.

This is to allow for easier branching of behaviour as more commands are
supported. Future iterations can look into creating a separate chatbot
class and instance separate from the main() function.

Duke:
- Remove all previous functions and replace with an echo() function.
- Standard messages are now stored as constants.

TaskList:
- markTask() and unmarkTask() now return String as output feedback.

Duke is refactored as many functions serve to only print a message.
It is redundant to create many functions to print to output.
echo() serves as a way to print output through the chatbot.

TaskList functions should return a message that will be sent as
feedback for the users. This is to make the chatbot feel more
responsive and users are aware of actions executed by chatbot.

ToDo: Task with no datetime attached.

Deadline: Task with a specified due date.

Event: Task with a specified start datetime and end datetime.

- User input to add tasks are now changed.
- TaskList addTask() function is slightly modified to immediately take
  in a created task.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add error handling and refactor task creation
commitResults.messageBody:
TaskException: Exceptions for when configuring tasks.

UnknownCommandException: Exception when user input unknown command.

Tasks are now created through factory methods from their respective
tasks. Tasks are also now created based on input directly after given
command.

This is to allow TaskExceptions to be thrown exclusively by Tasks
instead of the main program.
Prefer to run files from project root folder.

Also add such that adding and deleting tasks now outputs total number of
tasks left in the list.

Errors for delete task are also accounted for.

Duke program is handling all tasks.

It is good to have greater separation of concerns to reduce coupling.

Ui class helps separate printing of outputs.
Class is not yet used in program.

Code is tightly coupled with no clear separations of handling.

Command class are now introduced together with Parser and Storage
to better separate concerns. Additionally, TaskException is now renamed
as CommandException to better represent the exception.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix bug for unmark, mark and delete
commitResults.messageBody: Input was not trimmed before parsing, causing commands to fail.
